'''G<U+00E9>rard Paul Alain Feldzer''' (born 10 February 1944) is a consultant and aeronautical [[Popular science|popularizer]].  He is a former [[France|French]] [[airline pilot]], President of ''Comit<U+00E9> r<U+00E9>gional de tourisme d'<U+00CE>le-de-France'' (Regional Committee of [[<U+00CE>le-de-France (region)|<U+00CE>le-de-France]] Tourism) since May 2010,<ref name ="LP20072010" >{{fr}}[http://www.leparisien.fr/saint-denis-93200/une-femme-succede-a-gerard-feldzer-aumusee-de-l-air-20-07-2010-1006575.php Le Bourget : Une femme succ<U+00E8>de <U+00E0> G<U+00E9>rard Feldzer au mus<U+00E9>e de l<U+2019>Air]</ref> and Vice-Pr<U+00E9>sident of ''Ports de Paris'' (Ports of Paris).

He has also been Regional Advisor of [[<U+00CE>le-de-France (region)|<U+00CE>le-de-France]] for ''[[Europe <U+00C9>cologie]]''<ref>{{fr}}[http://europeecologielesverts-idf.fr/departements/hauts-de-seine-92/7140-gerard-feldzer/ G<U+00E9>rard Feldzer]</ref> since March 2010 and a close friend of [[Nicolas Hulot]].

== Biography ==

He started his career as an [[airline pilot]] at ''[[Air Alg<U+00E9>rie]]'' (1973<U+2013>1974) and moved to ''[[A<U+00E9>ropostale (aviation)|A<U+00E9>ropostale]]'' where he did night flights from 1974-1976. At Air France, he was a pilot on ''[[Sud Aviation Caravelle]]'', [[Boeing 707]] and [[Boeing 747|747]] aircrafts, [[Pilot in command|Captain]] (1989<U+2013>1992) then [[Pilot in command|Captain]] [[Flight instructor|Instructor]] (1992<U+2013>2004) on [[Airbus A310]], [[Airbus A340|A340]] and [[Airbus A330|A330]].

In 1985, he applied for an [[Astronaut]] job at [[CNES]] and was one of ten finalists.

He became President of the ''[[A<U+00E9>ro-Club de France]]''<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.aerobuzz.fr/spip.php?article1501 Les bons v<U+0153>ux de G<U+00E9>rard Feldzer]</ref> between 1995 and 2005.  The centenary of the club took place during his presidency, and he organized a major exhibition of planes in Paris on the ''[[Champs-<U+00C9>lys<U+00E9>es]]'' to celebrate it.

Between 2005 and August 2010, G<U+00E9>rard Feldzer was head of the ''[[Mus<U+00E9>e de l'Air]]'' (French Air and Space Museum) at [[Le Bourget]],.<ref>{{fr}}[http://defifutur.com/personne-gerard-feldzer G<U+00E9>rard Feldzer]</ref>  He made many animations and creations there including "''Planete Pilote''" ("Planet pilot"), the first space exhibition in the world aimed at 6-12 year olds.

He co-founded ''Zebunet'' (a micro-credit organisation for poor farmers in southern countries <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.zebu.net | title=Zebu.net | accessdate=14 April 2012}}</ref>) in 2001 and he has been its Vice-President since then. He also founded the "''Les ailes de la ville''" scheme, which provides training and integration for young suburban people through repairing and constructing aircraft.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://blog.museeairespace.fr/categorie/le-musee/les-ailes-de-la-ville-le-musee/ | title = Les ailes de la ville | accessdate=14 April 2012 | date=6 February 2012}}</ref>
As Founder and President of the "''Transports passion''" association, he has organized their annual meetings, exhibitions and events on ecomobility since 2005.<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.whoswho.fr/bio/gerard-feldzer_47075 G<U+00E9>rard Feldzer]</ref> 

On 1 January 2012, he became [[:Category:Officiers of the L<U+00E9>gion d'honneur|Officiers of the L<U+00E9>gion d'honneur]]<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.franceinfo.fr/politique-legion-d-honneur/legion-d-honneur-la-promotion-du-31-decembre-2011-486403-2012-01-03 L<U+00E9>gion d'honneur : la promotion du 31 d<U+00E9>cembre 2011]</ref>{{,}}.<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.scribd.com/doc/76873814/Journal-Officiel-du-dimanche-1er-janvier-2012 Journal Officiel du dimanche 1er janvier 2012]</ref>

== Media ==
=== Radio ===
Feldzer has had a weekly radio show on ''[[France Info]]'' since 2009.  Recent episodes include ''Circulez! il y a le monde <U+00E0> voir'' (Move! there is the world to see)).<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.franceinfo.fr/Gerard-Feldzer G<U+00E9>rard Feldzer sur France Info]</ref>

=== TV series ===
Feldzer wrote and directed the following series:

* ''Le Bar de l'escadrille'' ([[France 2]], 1985)
* ''Un ticket pour l'espace'' ([[France 2]], 1990)
* ''Les allum<U+00E9>s du sport'' ([[Canal+]] 1992)

and co-wrote the transport series ''Transportez moi'' in 2011, which aired on LCP TV in 2012.

=== Books ===
* ''Demain, je serai pilote''.<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.france5.fr/c-a-dire/index-fr.php?page=biographie&id_article=631 G<U+00E9>rard Feldzer]</ref>

== Bibliography ==

* ''Demain je serai pilote'', Gallimard, 1999 (ISBN 978-2-0705-2445-7)
* [[Acad<U+00E9>mie de l'air et de l'espace|Acad<U+00E9>mie nationale de l'air et de l'espace]] and Lucien Robineau, ''Les fran<U+00E7>ais du ciel, dictionnaire historique'', Le Cherche midi, June 2005, 782 p. (ISBN 2-7491-0415-7), p.&nbsp;212, ''FELDZER, G<U+00E9>rard''

